-- Armstrong, Citigroup, Verisk, Weatherford: U.S. Equity Preview
-- B y   I n y o u n g   H w a n g
-- 2012-03-23T21:10:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-23/armstrong-citigroup-verisk-weatherford-u-s-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in U.S. trading on March 26. Stock
symbols are in parentheses, and prices are as of 4:55 p.m. in
New York.  Armstrong World Industries Inc. (AWI)   rose 2.9 percent
to $58.47. The maker of floors, ceilings and cabinets said it
would pay a special cash dividend of $8.55 a share.  Citigroup Inc. (C US): The third-largest U.S. bank expects
an impairment charge of $700 million as the lender reduces an
investment in Istanbul-based Akbank TAS. The sum is about $1.1
billion before taxes, the New York-based lender said in a filing
with federal regulators.  Verisk Analytics Inc. (VRSK)  : The Jersey City, New
Jersey-based information services company will buy MediConnect
Global Inc., a provider of systems and services for medical-
record analysis, for $348.6 million.  Weatherford International Ltd. (WFT)   rose 2.5 percent to
$17.05. The oilfield-services and equipment provider named John
Briscoe, who joined the Geneva, Switzerland-based company in
August, as chief financial officer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Inyoung Hwang in  New York  at 
 ihwang7@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Baker at   nbaker7@bloomberg.net . 